deck: A thin razor of a man, Ebony Maw wins his battles not through the application of force, but through the webs of lies and manipulation he weaves. Though his methods are unconventional, his knack for results has earned him the respect of Thanos. He is one of the five generals of the Cull Obsidian.
description:
History

Ebony Maw is probably the most dangerous of Thanos' lieutenants of the Black Order, not because of his physical power but his mental power. A seducer and manipulator, Ebony Maw is a psychological mastermind.

Ebony Maw was sent after Doctor Strange as part of Thanos' invasion. This helped Maw learn the secrets of the Illuminati as well as the location of Thanos' son Thane, who was an Inhuman.

When Maw discovered Thane, he had just been exposed to the Terrigen Bomb and released his Inhuman power - the power of death. Maw saw this is a great opportunity to be more powerful with Thane at his control than working with Thanos. Maw designed a suit to contain Thane's power but also trapped him in an energy field. Ebony Maw gave Thane to Thanos as tribute.

While Thanos and the Cull Obsidian were in battle with the Avengers, Maw released Thane from his field to save the world from Thanos and thus use his powers of death. After Thane incased Thanos in a state of 'living death,' Maw and Thane left Earth to begin their move across the universe.

Powers & Abilities

Ebony Maw is known as a Whisperer and is a master of seduction and manipulation. He is able to infect the mind with mind webs, leaving behind a spider-like possession in the mind. Once there, it can gain secrets and control minds into doing his bidding. He is also a shrewd tactical genius who can weave a slew of impressive strategy's to ensure his need to handle things physically are unnecessary, enabling him to use others for the brunt of his dirty work instead.

Ebony Maw is not one for physical confrontations. He equips himself with a powerful forcefield and teleportation technology.

Other Media

He's one of the bosses in Marvel Avenger's Alliance, Facebook game.

deck: Choza Akimichi is a Jōnin ninja in Hidden Leaf Village and the father of Choji Akimichi.
description:
AppeaAppearance

Chōza is a tall, plump man with long, spiky red hair and purple markings on his cheeks — with the latter being a common trait in the Akimichi clan. He wears a samurai like outfit which entails a black su

it completed with armour that has the kanji for "food" (食, shoku) on it. He also wears a rope belt, hand-guards, and instead of a forehead protector — a hachimaki tied around his head. At some point in time, he also wore a pair of silver, hooped earrings before passing them down to his son. After they were returned to him when Chōji became a chūnin and swore his oath, he has not been seen wearing them.

When he uses the Multi-Size Technique two markings appear under his eyes; these markings disappear when he reverts to his normal size.[6][7]

Abilities

Like his son and the rest of his clan, Chōza uses the special technique that allows him to change calories into chakra. As the leader of his clan, it is highly logical that he is very skilled in all of his clan's secret techniques. He was able to provide assistance to Kakashi Hatake against the Deva Path, as well as put the Asura Path out of commission for most of the battle with a single hit after it was paralysed by Kakashi's Lightning Release: Shadow Clone Technique. Like most members of his clan, he also wields a bō in battle that has the ability to lengthen in proportion to him when he grows in size, with great proficiency. In the anime, he could use the bō to create a massive whirlwind that is strong enough to not only send dozens of enemies flying, but also Chōza himself while he uses his Multi-Size Technique. While hovering, his shadow covers almost the entire battlefield, which supports the techniques of his comrade Shikaku Nara.[8]

Physical Prowess

Chōza has an incredible amount of physical strength, displayed when he was able to stop Kinkaku's massive tail[6] as well as stop the Demonic Statue of the Outer Path with his bō, creating an opening for his son to attack it.[9] Chōza is also very durable and resistant to pain, using his body to deflect Asuma's explosive attack.[10]

Ninjutsu

Akimichi Clan Techniques

As the head of his clan, he is probably well versed in most, if not all, of his clan's techniques. He has demonstrated skill with the Multi-Size Technique able to stay in this form for an extended period of time without any noticeable strain on him or his chakra reserves and the Human Bullet Tank which he used alongside his son during their battle with Pain.[11] He has also used the Partial Multi-Size Technique to crush the Asura Path. All of these revolve around the clan's special ability to increase the size of their various body parts.

deck: Fuu is a ninja from the Hidden Waterfall Village and the Jinchūriki of the Seven-Tailed Horned Beetle.
description:
Origin

Fuu was a ninja from the Takigakure who was chosen to be the Jinchūriki of the Seven-Tailed Horned Beetle. She is the only ninja to be a Jinchūriki who wasn't from one of the five largest Shinoni Nations.

Creation

Fuu (フウ, Fuu) is a supporting character of the Naruto series that was created by Masashi Kishimoto, It first began serialization in Shueisha's Weekly Shonen Jump in November 1999. She was later introduced during the Five Kage Summit Arc story arc that began in Volume 45.

She first appeared in Naruto Volume 55, CH. 515 "The War Begins!".

Fuu's first series reveal is seen in the splash page for the cover of Naruto Vol. 45 Ch. 420, along with many of the other Jinchūriki. Her story reveal wouldn't be until much later in the series in Volume 55.

Character Evolution

Masashi Kishimoto designed Fuu with no real plan for the character's gender and has never formally addressed whether Fuu was to be a man or woman. The series has often been filled with sexually ambiguous characters. In concept art found in the Naruto 6: Road to Ninja movie, there is art that heavily implies she is female. A female voice actress was also selected for the anime and games.

In the series story, there is always a concern that the Jinchūriki could betray the village and leave with the power of the Tailed Beasts. It's been a tradition to select from the family of the village leaders. However, there is no Kage of the Takigakure. Her linage to the leader is unknown.

Major Story Arcs

At some point, Fuu was defeated and captured by the Akatsuki. By drawing out her Tailed-Beast. this is what caused her death.

Fourth Shinobi World War Arc

As part of the Akatsuki's plan to revive the Ten-Tails, Fuu and the other deceased Jinchūriki using the Edo Tense and implanted with the Rinnegan. They were all further controlled by the chakra receiver implanted in their bodies to be used as Obito Uchiha's version of the Six Paths of Pain. They were being used to try and capture Naruto Uzumaki and Killer Bee.

She aided in the fight against Naruto and Bee by blinding their vision with her Scaled Sneak Jutsu, and escaped being sealed by using her second version of the chakra cloak. After Kakashi Hatake and Might Guy came to reinforce Naruto, Fuu and the others were forced into their full Tailed Beast Mode to attack using the Biju Bomb.

As Naruto sought to free them all by removing the chakra receivers from their bodies, Fuu got to meet Naruto in another plain with Chōmei and the other Jinchūriki. As the Edo Tense was released, Fuu and the other were released back to the afterlife.

Powers & Abilities

As a kunoichi of the Takigakure, Fuu is likely a ninja of incredible skill in combat and ninjutsu abilities to be selected by the village as a Jinchūriki.

Fuu's Jutsu

  • Secret Tradition: Scaled Sneak Jutsu (秘伝・鱗粉隠れの術, Hiden: Rinpungakure no Jutsu): This technique is created by Fuu by expelling a fine powered from her mouth that has a luminous quality that can blind an opponent temporarily for attacks.

Jinchūriki Abilities

Various offensive and defensive abilities comes with being a Jinchūriki. It serves a source of chakra to be used to boost ninjutsu. With training, more power can be drawn out and controlled. A unique ability that comes with being the Jinchūriki of the Seven-Tailed Beetle is the ability of flight.

  • Tailed Beast Cloak Ver. 2 (バージョン2, Bājon Tsū): Fuu has shown the ability to use the second version of the Tailed-Beast Cloak. This covers the user's body in a dark chakra that comes from the beast sealed withing the Jinchūriki. This is only a partial transformation that keeps much of the user's human form.
  • Tailed Beast Mode (尾獣モード, Bijū Mōdo): The Tailed Beast Mode can only been used when the Jinchūriki has mastered control of their Tailed Beast's power. With this ability, they can take on the full form of the Tailed Beast.
  • Bug Bite (蟲食い , Mushikui): While in her chakra cloak mode version two, Fuu seemingly attacks with what appears to be a glancing blow that is actually a piercing bite.
  • Biju Bomb (尾獣玉, Bijūdama): The Biju Bomb is the ultimate offensive technique that is used among all the various Tailed-Beasts. This is created by molding positive black chakra (+の黒チャクラ, purasu no kuro chakura), and negative white chakra (−の白チャクラ, mainasu no shiro chakura) together. The power is then compressed. The opposing chakra must be balanced at an 8:2 ratio respectively or it will backfire.

Weapons & Equipment

Other Media

Anime

Naruto Shippuden (2007)

The Naruto Shippuden anime series is the second direct adaptation of Masashi Kishimoto's original manga. This series is produced by Studio Pierrot and first began airing in February 15, 2007. Fuu's first anime appearance was in Naruto Shippuden Episode 205 "Declaration of War", which aired on March 31, 2011. Her character in the Japanese series is voiced by Ryōko Shiraishi, and the U.S. dub produced by VIZ Media has yet to announce a voice actress.

Fuu's first appearance in the anime is far earlier set than her original manga appearance. She is shown during a montage for the various Tailed Beasts and their Jinchūriki. She has no spoken lines in this scene.

Games

Fuu's first appearance in video games is in Naruto Shippūden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 3 (ナルト- 疾風伝ナルティメットストーム3, Naruto Shippūden: Narutimetto Sutōmu 3). This fighting game was developed by Namco Bandai and released for the Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3. It was released in Japan in April 13, 2013, and in the U.S. in March 5, 2013. An enhanced edition called "Full Burst", is to be released in Europe during winter, available also for PC.

Since this game was released before Fuu's first voiced appearance in the anime, this is actually her first spoken role in the franchise. In the Japanese edition, Fuu is voiced by Ryōko Shiraishi, and the U.S. edition is performed by Kari Wahlgren.

deck: Elliot Caldwell was the sidekick to the original Wrath, a child sociopath twisted and molded in the anti-Batman's dark image. When his mentor perished in a battle with the Dark Knight, Caldwell took over the mantle of the Wrath and returned to Gotham to continue the original's mission.
description:
This page is for the second Wrath, Elliot Caldwell.

For the original, visit the Wrath page.

Wrath Child

When police officers start turning up dead all around Gotham and surveillance photos appear to incriminate Batman, Gordon and Batman think they have a copycat of the original Wrath. This new Wrath abducts Grayle Hudson, accusing her of betraying the original Wrath.

Batman catches up with Wrath and they fight to a standstill at which point he tells Batman to investigate what James Gordon was doing on June 26th twenty-five years ago. This enrages Batman and Wrath barely escapes when he forces Batman to save the life of Nightwing instead of pursuing him.

Gordon admits to having his records of that night wiped clean when the corrupt police force threatened to kill the boy. Gordon was then sent to Chicago, hoping to one day return and make things right by the boy he had orphaned.

Batman and Nightwing pursue Wrath to the airport where he had an elaborate death-trap prepared for the Batman and Grayle. The two escaped and the teamwork of Nightwing and Batman are able to easily defeat Wrath. Nightwing reveals Wrath's real name, Elliot Caldwell, and that the original Wrath had kidnapped him and four other boys to become his own 'Robin.' The other boys all died and only Elliot was left to carry on his legacy.

After his defeat, Caldwell was locked up in Blackgate Penitentiary.

Post-Flashpoint

The Wrath returned after the 2011 DC reboot in the pages of John Layman and Jason Fabok's Detective Comics #22. This version of Elliot Caldwell shares many similarities with his rival, the Batman: he is a billionaire, has spent unaccounted years abroad before returning to Gotham, and has his own armory much like the Dark Knight's, albeit more lethal variants of Wayne's gear.

Caldwell along with his partner were responsible for killing many of Gotham's police officers but by day he masqueraded as Elliot. D Caldwell, CEO and founder of Caldwell technologies and tried to buy Wayne Enterprises. After Batman defeated Scorn, Caldwell threw him out of his plane due to him disrupting his plans.

Wrath soon faced Batman after he was caught trying to kill a police officer. Wrath was able to use an electrical attack to incapacitate him. While under the guises of Bruce and Elliot, they sparred in a Hand to Hand fight with Bruce being able to defeat him, while giving Alfred time to search the building. However, Elliot knew of his plan all along and was able to use the technology he'd given Gotham Police Department against them and activated electrical attacks within them.

Wrath then went after Batman as he chased him in his plane through the streets of Gotham, forcing Batman to abandon his Bat-Plane to gain more time and caused it to self destruct and him to escape on his Bat-Glider. Alfred after having hacked Caldwell's files revealed to Bruce that Elliot's father had been killed by corrupt Gotham police officers.

Elliot later used his tank to bomb Gotham City Station, he then got out of his tank expecting to find a mass of dead police officers. Instead he found only Batman as Bruce had convinced James Gordon to evacuate the building. Batman in a modified suit similar in style to Wrath's proceeded to beat down Elliot, however, he didn't deliver the finishing blow. He instead allowed the Gotham Police Department to open fire on him and revealed to him that it was James Gordon who brought down the police officers who killed his father and proceeded to knock him out.

While he was in Blackgate Penitentiary, after a visit form James Gordon, Ignatius Ogilvy hints at them working together in the future.

Origin

The Boora Witch is a member of the White Martians. She had discovered a book of arcane knowledge and mastered the dark arts. This included the ability to place her consciousness in the body of another. Her own people grew fearful and exiled her to the Toonolian marshes.

Much later, the marshes was visited by Dejah Thoris and a search party, looking for precious metals. She placed her consciousness into Dejah Thoris, tried to cause a war between Helium and Zodanga and had Tardos Mors and Mors Kajak arrested so she could assume the throne. Kantos Kan discovered the truth and broke their bond when he beheaded the Witch's original body.

deck: Connelly is an agent of HYDRA who was involved with the project to restore Spider-Woman's powers. He was her handler and later tried to convince her to become the new Madame Hydra.
description:
Origin

HYDRA Connelly was an agent of who paid a visit to former superhero Jessica Drew and offered her the chance to regain her powers if she in turn would serve HYDRA as a double agent within S.H.I.E.L.D.

Creation

Connelly was created by Brian Michael Bendis. He first appeared in The New Avengers #6 albeit off-panel. He made subsequent appearances also off-panel and obscured and didn't make a full appearance until Giant-Size Spider-Woman #1 where he was drawn by Rick Mays.

Character Evolution

Connelly was a recurring character during The New Avengers series. With regards to retcons during Secret Invasion, the true nature of Connelly is some what confused and unclear. It is possible he was a Skrull or possibly just a unwitting pawn of the Skrulls who sought to replace Jessica Drew with their queen.

Powers and Abilities

When Connelly first confronted Jessica Drew, the two fought and Connelly displayed the ability to fire some form of energy blasts from his hands. This ability was never seen again or referred to, it's likely that he received the same treatments that Drew would receive and the blasts themselves were similar to her "venom blasts".

deck: Master mercenary of Helium.
description:
Origin

Gunbor was the master mercenary of Helium and taught others the skill. When his star pupil Tok Nur was murdered by Mortus, he went to investigate the legend of Mortus himself, disguising himself as Raf Nek. Dejah Thoris stowed away on his vessel to Zodanga, but she helped him expose Mortus. Upon entering Mortus' hideout, he was captured and transformed into one of the Machine Men. When Dejah Thoris almost underwent the same surgical treatment as Gunbor, he regained his free will and helped destroy several Machine Men, but was ultimately killed himself.
name: Gunbor
